Peruvian Ceviche
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 lb fresh fish (red snapper, grouper, halibut, etc)
3 1/2 tsp kosher salt, divided
3/4 c lime juice
2 tbsp evoo
2 garlic cloves, peeled
1 tbsp aji amarillo paste
8 oz radishesh, sliced thin
3 oranges, peeled, segmented, cut into 1/4" pieces
1/4 c coarsely chopped cilantro, for garnish
evoo for garnish

Cut fish into 1/2" strips, then 1/8" thick slices. Set 1/3 c fish aside, place the rest in medium bowl. Sprinkle 1 tsp salt over and toss gently. Cover with plastic wrap and let sit in refrigerator for 10-30 min. Place the reserved 1/3 c fish in blender with lime juice, oil, garlic, 2 1/2 tsp salt, and aji amarillo paste. Blend until smooth, ~30 s. Pour through fine mesh strainer. Add radishes, oranges, and fish to sauce in large bowl; toss gently. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30-60 min. Serve, topped with cilantro and evoo.



Notes: If you can't find aji amarillo, sub seeded habanero
